companyProfile.companyDescription: Kotak Mahindra Bank Limited is an India-based diversified financial services company. The Company's segments include Corporate/Wholesale Banking; Retail Banking; Treasury, BMU and Corporate Centre; Vehicle Financing; Other Lending Activities; Broking; Advisory and Transactional Services; Asset Management, and Insurance. Corporate/Wholesale Banking segment includes wholesale borrowings and lending and other related services to the corporate sector. Retail Banking segment comprises of digital banking and other retail banking. Vehicle Financing segment includes retail vehicle financing and wholesale trade financing to auto dealers. Other Lending Activities segment includes securitization and other loans/services. Advisory and Transactional Services segment provides financial advisory and transactional services such as mergers and acquisition advice, equity/debt issue management services and business correspondent services. Insurance segment includes life insurance and general insurance.

recentNews.headline: Kotak UPI RuPay Virtual Credit Card: Who can apply and how to get it instantly
recentNews.intro: Kotak Mahindra Bank?s UPI-linked RuPay Virtual Credit Card offers instant approval, lifetime free usage, UPI integration, and rewards, aligning with RBI?s push for seamless digital credit transactions.
recentNews.imagecaption: Kotak UPI RuPay Credit Card enables secure, reward-driven digital payments through UPI without the need for a physical card.

recentNews.headline: These five private banks in India have the lowest NPAs. Should you invest?
recentNews.intro: From an investment perspective, picking banks with low NPAs translates into a more stable and predictable earnings stream, a vital consideration when seeking reliable returns.
recentNews.imagecaption: NPAs or non-performing assets are loans and advances given by a bank to its customers that are default or close to being in default. (Image: Pixabay)

recentNews.headline: India's PSU banks outshine private peers in arresting bad loans
recentNews.intro: PSU banks not only saw a decline in fresh slippages in FY25 but also witnessed healthy recoveries and upgrades. Will the recovery continue going ahead?
recentNews.imagecaption: Bad loans of PSU banks decreased 16% year-on-year in FY25, (Image: Pixabay)

recentNews.headline: Kotak Mahindra Bank elevates Paritosh Kashyap to exec director; Shanti Ekambaram to retire on Oct 31
recentNews.intro: Kotak Mahindra Bank said that Shanti Ekambaram, Deputy Managing Director, will be retiring from her role effective October 31, 2025, upon completion of her current term.
recentNews.imagecaption: Kotak Mahindra Bank,Saket,New Delhi. PIC:MADHU KAPPARATH

recentNews.headline: Growth seen holding up as March quarter zips at 7.4%
recentNews.intro: Both figures were lower than year-on-year (y-o-y) compared to FY24, when Q4 recorded 7.8%, and full-year FY24 recorded GDP growth of 9.2% (revised).
recentNews.imagecaption: Chief economic advisor V. AnanthaNageswaran said India's steady, low-inflation growth condition is also leading to a record tightening of India's 10-year bond yield vis-a-vis the US 10-year treasury note yield.

recentNews.headline: How to get  ?3.5 lakh personal loan from Kotak Bank in just a few clicks
recentNews.intro: Kotak Mahindra Bank offers personal loans up to  ?35 lakh and higher with easy eligibility, quick approval, and digital application at competitive interest rates.
recentNews.imagecaption: Kotak Bank offers easy personal loan access online with fast approval and minimal documentation.

recentNews.headline: HDFC Bank, Axis to Kotak Bank: Why did ICICI Sec downgrade these top private lenders? Explained
recentNews.intro: Dalal Street darlings HDFC Bank, Axis Bank, and Kotak Mahindra Bank have just been downgraded by leading domestic brokerage ICICI Securities from 'Buy' to 'Add' amid weaker near-term performance expectations, especially around earnings growth.
recentNews.imagecaption: HDFC Bank, Axis to Kotak Bank: Why did ICICI Sec downgrade these top private lenders? Explained

recentNews.headline: Why the bond market is unfazed by a 22-year-low yield gap
recentNews.intro: Typically, when the yield gap shrinks, FPIs sell Indian bonds and invest in US bonds for risk-free returns. However, in recent years, India's sharply improving fiscal deficit and slowing inflation meant that Indian bond yields stayed stable while US yields spiked.
recentNews.imagecaption: Domestic macro stability is expected to shield India from any major outflows.

recentNews.headline: Shares to buy: Tata Motors to Kotak Bank - Prashanth Tapse suggests 3 stocks to buy in the short term
recentNews.intro: Shares to buy: Prashanth Tapse recommends buying these three stocks in the short term - Tata Motors, Titagarh Rail Systems, and Kotak Mahindra Bank.
recentNews.imagecaption: Shares to buy: Prashanth Tapse recommends buying these three stocks in the short term - Tata Motors, Titagarh Rail Systems, and Kotak Mahindra Bank.

recentNews.headline: In Q4, banks sailed through a tough quarter. But choppy waters await
recentNews.intro: Indian banks, such as ICICI and HDFC Bank, are showing remarkable resilience in a tough environment. Bank valuations, too, are near 10-year averages, offering a margin of safety. But there could be some ?unknown unknown? lurking in the shadows.
recentNews.imagecaption: Macroeconomic headwinds and the resultant slowdown in credit growth have been weighing on the domestic banking sector for the past few quarters.
